[
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "Hi. I'm Camille Moussette, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "designer on the Apple Design team. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this session, I will walk you through ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=14"
  },
  {
    "text": "the practical steps and design considerations ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=16"
  },
  {
    "text": "for adding audio and haptic feedback to an app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=18"
  },
  {
    "text": "Historically, it's been quite challenging both from a design ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "and engineering perspective to deliver rich app experiences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "that include animation, sound, and haptics. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=29"
  },
  {
    "text": "With Core Haptics on iPhone, it's now easier to create ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "magical moments that look, sound, and feel real. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "To explain and practice those skills, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=39"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll use an iOS app derived from a previous ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=41"
  },
  {
    "text": "code sample project called HapticBounce. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=44"
  },
  {
    "text": "A few additions were made to make it like ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=47"
  },
  {
    "text": "a mini game and to offer a canvas to design visual, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "sound, and haptics working well together. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "The new demo is called HapticRicochet.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "HapticRicochet is the story of a ball that comes to life ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the iPhone and moves around based on ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "the iPhone's orientations. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "The ball rolls around and bounces off the walls ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=69"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the phone with audio and haptic feedback, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=73"
  },
  {
    "text": "just like you expect in the physical world. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=76"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you tap the ball... ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "it grows into a larger ball. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=82"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you tap once more, a shield gets added to the ball. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "That shield gets damaged and depleted with each collision ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=88"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the walls, and ultimately the ball implodes and dies.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "We also added a texture to the background that you ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "enable or disable by tapping anywhere on the background. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=105"
  },
  {
    "text": "For this session, I will focus on only two mechanics: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=108"
  },
  {
    "text": "adding the shield and enabling the rolling texture. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "Before I proceed further, let's review the agenda. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll first review the key audio and haptic design principles ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "we often use within Apple. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=122"
  },
  {
    "text": "I will follow up with a brief introduction to Core Haptics, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=124"
  },
  {
    "text": "the framework that enables rich multimodal feedback.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "The core of the session will examine ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "the HapticRicochet project in Xcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "and see how one adds, designs, and refines ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "feedback for the shield and rolling texture moments. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "Designing multimodal experiences can be challenging, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=146"
  },
  {
    "text": "but when done well, it truly elevates the user experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=149"
  },
  {
    "text": "It feels magical, delightful, and just right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "One example is the Flashlight button in iOS. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "It combines visual animation, sound, and haptic feedback ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "in a unified experience that is clear, precise, and succinct. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=165"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's an iterative and creative process ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "that involves design and engineering effort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=173"
  },
  {
    "text": "Normally you would feel the haptics rather than hear them, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=176"
  },
  {
    "text": "but for demonstration purposes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=180"
  },
  {
    "text": "we've converted these haptics to sound ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=182"
  },
  {
    "text": "so you can hear it in this video. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "To help achieve magic and delight in your app experience, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=187"
  },
  {
    "text": "here are three principles to guide the work. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=190"
  },
  {
    "text": "They have been useful to us internally, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=193"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I hope they can help you as well. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=195"
  },
  {
    "text": "They are causality, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=198"
  },
  {
    "text": "harmony, and utility.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=200"
  },
  {
    "text": "For feedback to be useful, it must be obvious what caused it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's about making the source or the cause ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the feedback clear and obvious. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=211"
  },
  {
    "text": "The simplest form is getting feedback ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=213"
  },
  {
    "text": "as the ball hits the wall and the boundary of the phone. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=216"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's a collision with associated sound and haptics. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=219"
  },
  {
    "text": "Similarly, the haptics rolling texture is only presented ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=223"
  },
  {
    "text": "when the background visual is shown. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=226"
  },
  {
    "text": "You understand that the grid is what created that sensation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "Our second principle, harmony, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=234"
  },
  {
    "text": "highlights that our senses work best ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "when they are coherent, consistent, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=239"
  },
  {
    "text": "and working together to create a given experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=241"
  },
  {
    "text": "It should feel the way it looks, and the way it sounds. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=245"
  },
  {
    "text": "A small ball should feel small and sound small. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "A large ball ought to sound and feel heavier, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "like it has real extra mass. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=256"
  },
  {
    "text": "Our third principle, utility, is about providing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=260"
  },
  {
    "text": "clear value to your app experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=264"
  },
  {
    "text": "Don't add feedback just because you can. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "It can quickly become overwhelming and unpleasant. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=270"
  },
  {
    "text": "Reserve haptics and audio for significant moments ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=274"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your app, like the growth of the ball. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=277"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, let's review Core Haptics. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=281"
  },
  {
    "text": "Core Haptics is the technology on iPhone and iOS ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "that lets you design custom haptics ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=287"
  },
  {
    "text": "and audio feedback for your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=289"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's a powerful API centered around ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=291"
  },
  {
    "text": "four fundamental elements: engine, player, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=293"
  },
  {
    "text": "pattern, and event. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=297"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's review them briefly. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "The highest level element is the engine. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=303"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's our link to the physical actuator on the phone. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=306"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next we have a player. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=310"
  },
  {
    "text": "It is used for playback control, like start, stop, and pause. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=312"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then we have patterns and events. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=317"
  },
  {
    "text": "Patterns are a collection of events over time. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "Events are the building blocks used to specify the experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=323"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are many types of events. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "The most common ones are transient and continuous. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "Practically, here's a concrete example ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=333"
  },
  {
    "text": "of a pattern made of events. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm using the QuickLook Visualizer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=337"
  },
  {
    "text": "available in MacOS 12 to see the haptic pattern ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "specified in an .ahap file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=343"
  },
  {
    "text": "AHAP stands for Apple Haptic Audio Pattern. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=345"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's look at it again. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=349"
  },
  {
    "text": "Select an .ahap file in Finder, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=351"
  },
  {
    "text": "then press Space bar on your keyboard.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=354"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now let's look in detail at the items in the pattern. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=359"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first event in blue is a transient event. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=363"
  },
  {
    "text": "The second event in orange is a continuous event.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=368"
  },
  {
    "text": "The pattern is using JSON syntax. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=374"
  },
  {
    "text": "The transient event is created from this code.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=376"
  },
  {
    "text": "This sums up our overview of Core Haptics. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=381"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more in-depth information, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=385"
  },
  {
    "text": "check out the documentation online. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=386"
  },
  {
    "text": "For the practice in this session, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=389"
  },
  {
    "text": "we'll focus on loading, changing, and playing patterns. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=391"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's time for Xcode and the HapticRicochet. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=395"
  },
  {
    "text": "Open the project from HapticRicochet-Start folder. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=397"
  },
  {
    "text": "Make sure you can compile and run the project on your iPhone. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=402"
  },
  {
    "text": "The simulator doesn't work for haptics. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=406"
  },
  {
    "text": "You need a physical iPhone 8 or newer to feel the haptics. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=409"
  },
  {
    "text": "Verify that the phone is not silenced ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=413"
  },
  {
    "text": "and that the volume level is high. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=415"
  },
  {
    "text": "The plan is to work with ViewController files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=418"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the .ahap, .wav and .png asset files. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=421"
  },
  {
    "text": "Make sure you familiarize yourself ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=426"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the game and all its interactions. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=428"
  },
  {
    "text": "Remember, you can tap the ball, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=430"
  },
  {
    "text": "tap the background, and tilt the phone around. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=435"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=438"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you're ready, let's dive into the shield transformation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=440"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll use the harmony principle to dissect ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=444"
  },
  {
    "text": "the shield moment and look at the design details. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=446"
  },
  {
    "text": "For visual, we have an animation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=450"
  },
  {
    "text": "that is 500 milliseconds in duration ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=451"
  },
  {
    "text": "and that looks like this in the upper right.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=454"
  },
  {
    "text": "For haptic, we'll want to highlight ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=458"
  },
  {
    "text": "the transformation to a new state. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=460"
  },
  {
    "text": "For audio, we want to convey a gain ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=463"
  },
  {
    "text": "in energy and an end state that is robust and protected.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=465"
  },
  {
    "text": "For this practice, we've created two different assets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=471"
  },
  {
    "text": "that convey different qualities. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=474"
  },
  {
    "text": "We'll look at them and see what works best ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=476"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the shield experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "But first, let's look at how we load ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=480"
  },
  {
    "text": "and play feedback for shield.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=482"
  },
  {
    "text": "Functionally, the code is divided in two parts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=486"
  },
  {
    "text": "We first initialize our building blocks and, second, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=490"
  },
  {
    "text": "a function to play and render that shield transformation.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the initializeShieldHaptics function, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=498"
  },
  {
    "text": "I first create a pattern from a ShieldTransient file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=500"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then create a shieldPlayer with that pattern.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=504"
  },
  {
    "text": "The feedback is ready to play at this point.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=509"
  },
  {
    "text": "The function shield is called ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=513"
  },
  {
    "text": "when the transformation is ready to be rendered. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "The haptic and audio feedback are played via ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=518"
  },
  {
    "text": "calling startPlayer on our shieldPlayer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=521"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's a convenience function we reuse frequently in the project. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=524"
  },
  {
    "text": "The visual animation is then played.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=528"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now let's look at our ShieldTransient asset. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=532"
  },
  {
    "text": "It defines the experience we have ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=536"
  },
  {
    "text": "for haptic and audio feedback. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=537"
  },
  {
    "text": "The haptic should feel like this: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=540"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=542"
  },
  {
    "text": "And the audio should sound like this: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=543"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=546"
  },
  {
    "text": "I like the sound. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=547"
  },
  {
    "text": "It feels like a gain of robustness ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=548"
  },
  {
    "text": "and protection for the ball. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=550"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's hear it again. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=552"
  },
  {
    "text": "The problem is the haptic and the sound ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=554"
  },
  {
    "text": "don't really match. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=556"
  },
  {
    "text": "The haptic is made of three transients... ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=557"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=559"
  },
  {
    "text": "While the audio is continuous and progressive. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=560"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=563"
  },
  {
    "text": "There's no harmony between the two senses. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=564"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=566"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's look at the alternate asset ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=568"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is called ShieldContinuous. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=570"
  },
  {
    "text": "It has a continuous haptic progression... ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=573"
  },
  {
    "text": "And a wobbly audio that decays. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=575"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=578"
  },
  {
    "text": "Again, I can feel and hear ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=579"
  },
  {
    "text": "that the haptic and audio don't really match. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=581"
  },
  {
    "text": "But I like the haptic. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=584"
  },
  {
    "text": "It feels like a good transformation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=586"
  },
  {
    "text": "for gaining a shield. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=588"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's hear the haptic again. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=590"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=592"
  },
  {
    "text": "My plan is to use that continuous haptic pattern ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=593"
  },
  {
    "text": "but use the sound from the first asset.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=596"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll use the two assets and take the audio I like ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=600"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the first pattern ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=602"
  },
  {
    "text": "and use it in the second continuous haptic pattern.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=604"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's see how I do that in practice.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=608"
  },
  {
    "text": "First I open the ShieldContinuous.ahap file ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=611"
  },
  {
    "text": "in a text editor and scroll to the end of the file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=615"
  },
  {
    "text": "You'll see this event where we specify the audio file ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=618"
  },
  {
    "text": "to play with the haptics.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=622"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's using the EventType AudioCustom ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a filename for the audio file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=629"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can specify and adjust the volume ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=631"
  },
  {
    "text": "using a ParameterValue.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=634"
  },
  {
    "text": "To use the preferred audio, I change ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=638"
  },
  {
    "text": "the file reference from ShieldB.wav to ShieldA.wav.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=641"
  },
  {
    "text": "The revised and final asset looks like this. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=649"
  },
  {
    "text": "The haptic... ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=652"
  },
  {
    "text": "and audio are coherent. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=655"
  },
  {
    "text": "They support and reinforce each other. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=658"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's listen to the combined audio and haptics together. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=661"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=665"
  },
  {
    "text": "The last change needed is to use that final asset I just created. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=667"
  },
  {
    "text": "I go back to InitializeShieldHaptics function ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=671"
  },
  {
    "text": "and instead of using ShieldTransient, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=675"
  },
  {
    "text": "I specify and load the ShieldContinuous file.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=678"
  },
  {
    "text": "Voilà! Here we have it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=683"
  },
  {
    "text": "I now compile and run on device. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=686"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=689"
  },
  {
    "text": "I end up with a harmonious shield transformation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=691"
  },
  {
    "text": "that feels just right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=694"
  },
  {
    "text": "The haptic, audio, and visual are working well together ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=696"
  },
  {
    "text": "to convey the addition of shield protection to the ball. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=699"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, I'll review how to add the rolling texture to the app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=703"
  },
  {
    "text": "HapticRicochet starts with no rolling texture, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=709"
  },
  {
    "text": "just collision with the walls. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=712"
  },
  {
    "text": "If I tap on the background, the polka dot texture shows up, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=715"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I get additional haptic feedback ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=718"
  },
  {
    "text": "as the ball rolls around. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=721"
  },
  {
    "text": "We'll encounter and resolve two issues moving forward, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=723"
  },
  {
    "text": "one of a technical nature. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=726"
  },
  {
    "text": "The other one relates to the design of the experience.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=729"
  },
  {
    "text": "In the initializeTextureHaptics function, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=735"
  },
  {
    "text": "I first create a pattern from the texture ahap file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=737"
  },
  {
    "text": "I then create a ShieldPlayer with that pattern. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=742"
  },
  {
    "text": "The function updateTexturePlayer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=746"
  },
  {
    "text": "is called on every frame the texture is active. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=748"
  },
  {
    "text": "We use it to update the intensity of the haptic ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=752"
  },
  {
    "text": "based on the speed of the ball. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=755"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's look at the results. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=757"
  },
  {
    "text": "The issue I'm noticing is the texture goes away ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=760"
  },
  {
    "text": "after a few seconds. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=763"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=765"
  },
  {
    "text": "I know why it's happening like this. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=768"
  },
  {
    "text": "There's an easy way to fix that behavior. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=770"
  },
  {
    "text": "The issue we have is that the texture ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=773"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the .ahap files has only 2 seconds of haptic content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=776"
  },
  {
    "text": "There's a way to change that behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=780"
  },
  {
    "text": "and make it play endlessly. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=782"
  },
  {
    "text": "The advanced variant of the pattern player ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=785"
  },
  {
    "text": "offers additional functionalities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=787"
  },
  {
    "text": "like pause, resume, and other callbacks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=790"
  },
  {
    "text": "In HapticRicochet, I will use the advanced ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=794"
  },
  {
    "text": "pattern player only for its looping capabilities. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=797"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's walk through this change. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=801"
  },
  {
    "text": "I first modify the declaration of texturePlayer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=804"
  },
  {
    "text": "to be of CHHapticAdvancedPatternPlayer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=807"
  },
  {
    "text": "type. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=809"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then I'll use the same texture file, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=812"
  },
  {
    "text": "but this time, creating an AdvancedPlayer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=815"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can now enable the looping behavior on that AdvancedPlayer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=818"
  },
  {
    "text": "The nice thing is that the rest of the code stays all the same. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=823"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's look at the results. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=827"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=831"
  },
  {
    "text": "The rolling texture plays in a loop this time ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=835"
  },
  {
    "text": "with no apparent pause or seam. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=838"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=840"
  },
  {
    "text": "The second issue I want to address is related to ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=844"
  },
  {
    "text": "the look and feel of the texture. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=847"
  },
  {
    "text": "We see that our haptic pattern asset is quite dense, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=849"
  },
  {
    "text": "with nearly 100 entries over 2 seconds. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=853"
  },
  {
    "text": "Our visual background texture is very coarse, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=856"
  },
  {
    "text": "with just a few dots across. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=859"
  },
  {
    "text": "I think the experience would be improved and more ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=861"
  },
  {
    "text": "realistic if the dot pattern would be more dense.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=863"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll change the resource file we used ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=869"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the backgroundImage to use the Fine version of this file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=871"
  },
  {
    "text": "If I run the app, the new denser texture will be used. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=875"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a look. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=879"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=881"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you run into issues or problems, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=890"
  },
  {
    "text": "we've included the final version of the project ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=892"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the HapticRicochet-Final folder. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=895"
  },
  {
    "text": "It has all the changes we've made during this session, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=897"
  },
  {
    "text": "ready to compile and feel on your iPhone. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=901"
  },
  {
    "text": "There is still room for you to explore ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=906"
  },
  {
    "text": "and design your own haptic experiences. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=908"
  },
  {
    "text": "I invite you to look at the other transformation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=910"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the game and try to design your own ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=912"
  },
  {
    "text": "new haptic and sound feedback for them. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=915"
  },
  {
    "text": "To recap, I introduced audio and haptic ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=918"
  },
  {
    "text": "design principles that can guide you to design ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=921"
  },
  {
    "text": "great multimodal experiences in your app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=923"
  },
  {
    "text": "I reviewed the fundamentals of Core Haptics, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=926"
  },
  {
    "text": "the API to add custom feedback in iOS. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=928"
  },
  {
    "text": "I've put them in practice using the HapticRicochet project, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=932"
  },
  {
    "text": "focusing on the shield and rolling texture mechanics. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=936"
  },
  {
    "text": "For additional information and resources, please refer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=939"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the Human Interface Guideline, and the Developer documentation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=942"
  },
  {
    "text": "Lastly, you can revisit the WWDC 2019 session ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=946"
  },
  {
    "text": "covering the launch of Core Haptics. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=951"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you for watching. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=953"
  },
  {
    "text": "[percussive music]",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10278/?time=955"
  }
]